<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Thiago Alcantara has bid an emotional farewell to Bayern Munich's fans ahead of his £25m to Liverpool. </p>

<p>Having been linked with the Spaniard all summer, Liverpool finally made a breakthrough in their negotiations with Bayern on Thursday after they agreed to pay a minimum of £20m over the next four years, along with £5m in add-ons.</p>

<p>The 29-year-old was made available by Bayern after he entered the final year of his contract, but posting on Twitter he bid an emotional goodbye to the Bundesliga giants. </p>

<p>Thiago Alcantara has bid an emotional farewell to Bayern Munich ahead of his Liverpool move</p>

<p>'Yes, I've made the most difficult decision of my sporting career,' he said.</p>

<p>'I will close this chapter in this wonderful club, the club where I grew and developed myself as a player during the last seven years.</p>

<p>'Victories, success, joyful moments and some hard times as well. But what I am most proud of is having arrived in Munich being a young man full of dreams full of dreams and leaving completely fulfilled and identified with a club, a history, a philosophy, a language and a culture.</p>

<p>'Here I learnt how to love and respect a tradition which I say goodbye now but I will never forget the Mia San Mia.</p>

<p>Liverpool finally made a breakthrough in negotiations to sign the Champions League winner</p>

<p>'Me and my family have lived amazing moments in the city, at Sabener Strasse, and of course, in our beloved Allianz Arena.</p>

<p>'With you, my Bayern family who treated me so well and loved me every second.</p>

<p>'My decision is purely sports related. As a football player, I want and I need new challenges in order to develop myself as I did here.</p>

<p>'Bayern will always be my heimat, Eternal Thanks to you, Bayern.' </p>
